  "response": "Yes, in most legal systems, there is a distinction between intentional and unintentional money laundering. Intentional money laundering typically involves knowingly engaging in financial transactions to conceal the source of illegally obtained funds, and carries more severe criminal penalties. Unintentional money laundering might involve accidentally facilitating money laundering without criminal intent, which could result in civil penalties or lesser consequences. The specific treatment varies by jurisdiction, but intent is generally a key factor in determining the legal response.",
